<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Chemical Usage in Vegetables & Fruits</h1>
        <p>Understanding the types, causes, effects, and precautions</p>
    </header>

    <section class="types">
        <h2>Types of Chemical Usage</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Pest Control</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like insecticides and pesticides are used to kill insects that damage crops.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Fungal Disease Control</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like fungicides are used to prevent fungal diseases that can spoil crops.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Ripening Agents</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like ethylene and ethephon are used to ripen fruits, making them ready for consumption.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Preservation</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like waxes and preservatives are used to extend the shelf life of fruits and vegetables.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="causes">
        <h2>Causes of Chemical Usage</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Crop Protection</h3>
                <p>Pest infestations and diseases can damage crops, leading to the use of chemicals like insecticides and fungicides.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Yield Enhancement</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like fertilizers and growth regulators are used to promote plant growth and increase yields.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Post-Harvest Management</h3>
                <p>Chemicals like waxes and preservatives are used to extend shelf life and maintain quality after harvesting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Market Demand</h3>
                <p>Chemicals may be used to improve appearance, texture, and freshness of produce to meet consumer expectations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="effects">
        <h2>Effects of Chemical Usage</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card positive">
                <h3>Positive Effects</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Increased crop yields:</strong> Chemicals help control pests and diseases, leading to higher yields.</li>
                    <li><strong>Improved appearance:</strong> Enhances the look of produce, making it more attractive.</li>
                    <li><strong>Extended shelf life:</strong> Preservatives and waxes help keep fruits and vegetables fresh longer.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card negative">
                <h3>Negative Effects</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Health risks:</strong> Chemical residues may cause cancer, neurological damage, and other health issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Environmental impact:</strong> Contaminates soil, water, and air, harming ecosystems.</li>
                    <li><strong>Pesticide-resistant pests:</strong> Overuse leads to pests becoming harder to control.</li>
                    <li><strong>Harm to beneficial insects:</strong> Chemicals can kill bees and butterflies, essential for pollination.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="precautions">
        <h2>Precautions for Chemical Usage</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Follow Label Instructions</h3>
                <p>Always follow the instructions on the chemical label.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Wear Protective Gear</h3>
                <p>Use protective clothing, gloves, and masks when handling chemicals.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Observe Pre-Harvest Intervals</h3>
                <p>Ensure sufficient time passes between chemical application and harvest.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Wash Produce</h3>
                <p>Wash fruits and vegetables thoroughly before consumption to reduce residue exposure.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

